1 d. to quiet title, to establish a trust in, remove a
2 cloud on, set aside a conveyance of, or to enforce or
3 set aside an agreement to convey real property; and
4 2. For all damages to land, crops, or improvements thereon,
5 actions shall be brought in the county where the damage occurs; and
6 3. For disputes related to repairs or improvements made on real
7 property or fixtures attached to real property, actions shall be
8 brought in the county where the real property is located.
9 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
10 Passed the Senate the 12th day of March, 2025.
